  "response": "Here are some cheese rinds that are generally safe to eat:\n\n1. Edible rinds:\n- Brie rind\n- Camembert rind\n- Parmesan rind\n- Gouda rind\n- Aged cheddar rind\n- Gruy\u00e8re rind\n\n2. Rinds often eaten:\n- Manchego rind\n- Pecorino rind\n\n3. Rinds to avoid:\n- Waxed rinds\n- Plastic-coated rinds\n- Very hard or waxy rinds\n- Rinds with mold not intentionally part of the cheese\n\nAlways ensure the rind looks and smells appetizing. When in doubt, you can remove the rind and just enjoy the cheese inside.\n\nSome people add Parmesan rinds to soups and stews for extra flavor. Some rinds are more tasty and digestible than others, so personal preference plays a role.",
